{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":794,"text":"About 10 years ago, I went through\na little bit of a hard time."},{"time":4175,"text":"So I decided to go see a therapist."},{"time":6473,"text":"I had been seeing her for a few months,\nwhen she looked at me one day and said,"},{"time":10219,"text":"\"Who actually raised you\nuntil you were three?\""},{"time":14202,"text":"Seemed like a weird question.\nI said, \"My parents.\""},{"time":17890,"text":"And she said, \"I don't think\nthat's actually the case;"},{"time":21172,"text":"because if it were,"},{"time":22353,"text":"we'd be dealing with things that are\nfar more complicated than just this.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":26906,"text":"It sounded like the setup to a joke,\nbut I knew she was serious."},{"time":30948,"text":"Because when I first started seeing her,"},{"time":33224,"text":"I was trying to be\nthe funniest person in the room."},{"time":35854,"text":"And I would try and crack these jokes,\nbut she caught on to me really quickly,"},{"time":40036,"text":"and whenever I tried to make a joke,\nshe would look at me and say,"},{"time":43837,"text":"\"That is actually really sad.\""},{"time":46991,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":48912,"text":"It's terrible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50557,"text":"So I knew I had to be serious,\nand I asked my parents"},{"time":54068,"text":"who had actually raised me\nuntil I was three?"},{"time":56666,"text":"And to my surprise, they said"},{"time":59064,"text":"my primary caregiver had been\na distant relative of the family."},{"time":63291,"text":"I had called her my auntie."}]},{"cues":[{"time":66502,"text":"I remember my auntie so clearly,"},{"time":68611,"text":"it felt like she had been part of my life\nwhen I was much older."},{"time":72312,"text":"I remember the thick, straight hair,"},{"time":74663,"text":"and how it would come around\nme like a curtain"},{"time":76949,"text":"when she bent to pick me up;"},{"time":78314,"text":"her soft, southern Thai accent;"},{"time":80876,"text":"the way I would cling to her,"},{"time":82730,"text":"even if she just wanted to go\nto the bathroom"},{"time":84873,"text":"or get something to eat."},{"time":86922,"text":"I loved her, but [with] the ferocity\nthat a child has sometimes"},{"time":90552,"text":"before she understands that love\nalso requires letting go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96807,"text":"But my clearest and sharpest\nmemory of my auntie,"},{"time":100267,"text":"is also one of my first\nmemories of life at all."},{"time":104345,"text":"I remember her being beaten and slapped\nby another member of my family."},{"time":109686,"text":"I remember screaming hysterically\nand wanting it to stop,"},{"time":112607,"text":"as I did every single time it happened,"},{"time":115405,"text":"for things as minor as wanting\nto go out with her friends,"},{"time":118166,"text":"or being a little late."},{"time":120856,"text":"I became so hysterical over her treatment,"},{"time":123292,"text":"that eventually, she was just\nbeaten behind closed doors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":129634,"text":"Things got so bad for her\nthat eventually she ran away."},{"time":133424,"text":"As an adult, I learned later"},{"time":135020,"text":"that she had been just 19\nwhen she was brought over from Thailand"},{"time":139271,"text":"to the States to care for me,\non a tourist visa."},{"time":143674,"text":"She wound up working\nin Illinois for a time,"},{"time":145755,"text":"before eventually returning to Thailand,"},{"time":148209,"text":"which is where I ran into her again,\nat a political rally in Bangkok."},{"time":153159,"text":"I clung to her again, as I had\nwhen I was a child,"},{"time":156616,"text":"and I let go, and then\nI promised that I would call."},{"time":161079,"text":"I never did, though."},{"time":163536,"text":"Because I was afraid if I said\neverything that she meant to me --"},{"time":168327,"text":"that I owed perhaps the best parts\nof who I became to her care,"},{"time":173101,"text":"and that the words \"I'm sorry\"\nwere like a thimble"},{"time":176213,"text":"to bail out all the guilt\nand shame and rage I felt"},{"time":180662,"text":"over everything she had endured\nto care for me for as long as she had --"},{"time":186410,"text":"I thought if I said those words to her,\nI would never stop crying again."},{"time":192304,"text":"Because she had saved me."},{"time":194870,"text":"And I had not saved her."}]},{"cues":[{"time":200877,"text":"I'm a journalist, and I've been writing\nand researching human trafficking"},{"time":204345,"text":"for the past eight years or so,"},{"time":206470,"text":"and even so, I never put together\nthis personal story"},{"time":210445,"text":"with my professional life\nuntil pretty recently."},{"time":214234,"text":"I think this profound disconnect\nactually symbolizes"},{"time":217577,"text":"most of our understanding\nabout human trafficking."},{"time":220977,"text":"Because human trafficking is far more\nprevalent, complex and close to home"},{"time":226628,"text":"than most of us realize."}]},{"cues":[{"time":229377,"text":"I spent time in jails and brothels,"},{"time":231393,"text":"interviewed hundreds of survivors\nand law enforcement, NGO workers."},{"time":235578,"text":"And when I think about what we've done\nabout human trafficking,"},{"time":238579,"text":"I am hugely disappointed."},{"time":241284,"text":"Partly because we don't even talk\nabout the problem right at all."},{"time":246185,"text":"When I say \"human trafficking,\""},{"time":248011,"text":"most of you probably don't think\nabout someone like my auntie."},{"time":251834,"text":"You probably think\nabout a young girl or woman,"},{"time":254575,"text":"who's been brutally forced\ninto prostitution by a violent pimp."},{"time":259009,"text":"That is real suffering,\nand that is a real story."},{"time":263578,"text":"That story makes me angry"},{"time":264885,"text":"for far more than just the reality\nof that situation, though."}]},{"cues":[{"time":269560,"text":"As a journalist, I really care about how\nwe relate to each other through language,"},{"time":274396,"text":"and the way we tell that story,\nwith all the gory, violent detail,"},{"time":278111,"text":"the salacious aspects -- I call that\n\"look at her scars\" journalism."},{"time":283782,"text":"We use that story to convince ourselves"},{"time":286064,"text":"that human trafficking is a bad man\ndoing a bad thing to an innocent girl."},{"time":291328,"text":"That story lets us off the hook."},{"time":293248,"text":"It takes away all the societal context\nthat we might be indicted for,"},{"time":297010,"text":"for the structural inequality,\nor the poverty,"},{"time":299193,"text":"or the barriers to migration."},{"time":301689,"text":"We let ourselves think"},{"time":302864,"text":"that human trafficking is only\nabout forced prostitution,"},{"time":306464,"text":"when in reality,"},{"time":308003,"text":"human trafficking is embedded\nin our everyday lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312771,"text":"Let me show you what I mean."},{"time":314996,"text":"Forced prostitution accounts for\n22 percent of human trafficking."},{"time":319828,"text":"Ten percent is in state-\nimposed forced labor."},{"time":323823,"text":"but a whopping 68 percent\nis for the purpose of creating the goods"},{"time":328010,"text":"and delivering the services\nthat most of us rely on every day,"},{"time":332664,"text":"in sectors like agricultural work,\ndomestic work and construction."},{"time":337298,"text":"That is food and care and shelter."},{"time":341067,"text":"And somehow, these most essential workers"},{"time":343453,"text":"are also among the world's most underpaid\nand exploited today."},{"time":349430,"text":"Human trafficking is the use\nof force, fraud or coercion"},{"time":353917,"text":"to compel another person's labor."},{"time":356470,"text":"And it's found in cotton fields,\nand coltan mines,"},{"time":359268,"text":"and even car washes in Norway and England."},{"time":362245,"text":"It's found in U.S. military\nbases in Iraq and Afghanistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":366171,"text":"It's found in Thailand's fishing industry."},{"time":368726,"text":"That country has become the largest\nexporter of shrimp in the world."},{"time":373248,"text":"But what are the circumstances"},{"time":375598,"text":"behind all that cheap\nand plentiful shrimp?"},{"time":379724,"text":"Thai military were caught selling\nBurmese and Cambodian migrants"},{"time":383989,"text":"onto fishing boats."},{"time":385944,"text":"Those fishing boats were taken out,\nthe men put to work,"},{"time":389065,"text":"and they were thrown overboard\nif they made the mistake of falling sick,"},{"time":392741,"text":"or trying to resist their treatment."},{"time":395368,"text":"Those fish were then used to feed shrimp,"},{"time":397887,"text":"The shrimp were then sold\nto four major global retailers:"},{"time":402345,"text":"Costco, Tesco, Walmart and Carrefour."}]},{"cues":[{"time":409251,"text":"Human trafficking is found\non a smaller scale than just that,"},{"time":412474,"text":"and in places you would\nnever even imagine."},{"time":415016,"text":"Traffickers have forced young people\nto drive ice cream trucks,"},{"time":418025,"text":"or to sing in touring boys' choirs."},{"time":420953,"text":"Trafficking has even been found\nin a hair braiding salon in New Jersey."}]},{"cues":[{"time":424942,"text":"The scheme in that case was incredible."},{"time":427522,"text":"The traffickers found young families\nwho were from Ghana and Togo,"},{"time":433647,"text":"and they told these families that\n\"your daughters are going to get"},{"time":437013,"text":"a fine education in the United States.\""},{"time":439718,"text":"They then located winners\nof the green card lottery,"},{"time":442400,"text":"and they told them, \"We'll help you out."},{"time":445285,"text":"We'll get you a plane ticket.\nWe'll pay your fees."},{"time":448288,"text":"All you have to do is take\nthis young girl with you,"},{"time":451284,"text":"say that she's your sister or your spouse."},{"time":454998,"text":"Once everyone arrived in New Jersey,\nthe young girls were taken away,"},{"time":458285,"text":"and put to work for 14-hour days,"},{"time":460868,"text":"seven days a week, for five years."},{"time":464154,"text":"They made their traffickers\nnearly four million dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":470345,"text":"This is a huge problem."},{"time":472491,"text":"So what have we done about it?"},{"time":475049,"text":"We've mostly turned\nto the criminal justice system."},{"time":478386,"text":"But keep in mind, most victims of human\ntrafficking are poor and marginalized."},{"time":482418,"text":"They're migrants, people of color."},{"time":484448,"text":"Sometimes they're in the sex trade."},{"time":486634,"text":"And for populations like these,"},{"time":488824,"text":"the criminal justice system is\ntoo often part of the problem,"},{"time":491886,"text":"rather than the solution."},{"time":494444,"text":"In study after study, in countries ranging\nfrom Bangladesh to the United States,"},{"time":499113,"text":"between 20 and 60 percent of the people\nin the sex trade who were surveyed"},{"time":503874,"text":"said that they had been raped or assaulted\nby the police in the past year alone."},{"time":510302,"text":"People in prostitution, including people\nwho have been trafficked into it,"},{"time":513993,"text":"regularly receive multiple\nconvictions for prostitution."},{"time":517809,"text":"Having that criminal record makes it\nso much more difficult"},{"time":520897,"text":"to leave poverty, leave abuse,\nor leave prostitution,"},{"time":524818,"text":"if that person so desires."},{"time":528296,"text":"Workers outside of the sex sector --"},{"time":530256,"text":"if they try and resist their treatment,\nthey risk deportation."},{"time":535146,"text":"In case after case I've studied,\nemployers have no problem"},{"time":538352,"text":"calling on law enforcement\nto try and threaten or deport"},{"time":541819,"text":"their striking trafficked workers."},{"time":544718,"text":"If those workers run away,"},{"time":546496,"text":"they risk becoming part of the great mass\nof undocumented workers"},{"time":551232,"text":"who are also subject to the whims\nof law enforcement if they're caught."}]},{"cues":[{"time":557670,"text":"Law enforcement is supposed to identify\nvictims and prosecute traffickers."},{"time":564033,"text":"But out of an estimated 21 million victims\nof human trafficking in the world,"},{"time":568743,"text":"they have helped and identified\nfewer than 50,000 people."},{"time":573742,"text":"That's like comparing"},{"time":575385,"text":"the population of the world\nto the population of Los Angeles,"},{"time":579280,"text":"proportionally speaking."},{"time":581997,"text":"As for convictions, out of an estimated\n5,700 convictions in 2013,"},{"time":588443,"text":"fewer than 500 were for labor trafficking."},{"time":591976,"text":"Keep in mind that labor trafficking"},{"time":593692,"text":"accounts for 68 percent\nof all trafficking,"},{"time":596882,"text":"but fewer than 10 percent\nof the convictions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602161,"text":"I've heard one expert say that trafficking\nhappens where need meets greed."},{"time":607523,"text":"I'd like to add one more element to that."},{"time":610772,"text":"Trafficking happens in sectors where\nworkers are excluded from protections,"},{"time":614951,"text":"and denied the right to organize."},{"time":617874,"text":"Trafficking doesn't happen in a vacuum."},{"time":620538,"text":"It happens in systematically\ndegraded work environments."},{"time":625249,"text":"You might be thinking,"},{"time":626424,"text":"oh, she's talking about failed states,\nor war-torn states, or --"},{"time":629549,"text":"I'm actually talking\nabout the United States."},{"time":632270,"text":"Let me tell you what that looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635342,"text":"I spent many months researching\na trafficking case called Global Horizons,"},{"time":638859,"text":"involving hundreds of Thai farm workers."},{"time":641209,"text":"They were sent all over the States,\nto work in Hawaii pineapple plantations,"},{"time":644825,"text":"and Washington apple orchards,\nand anywhere the work was needed."},{"time":648555,"text":"They were promised three years\nof solid agricultural work."},{"time":652903,"text":"So they made a calculated risk."},{"time":654847,"text":"They sold their land, they sold\ntheir wives' jewelry,"},{"time":657953,"text":"to make thousands in recruitment fees\nfor this company, Global Horizons."},{"time":662776,"text":"But once they were brought over,"},{"time":664628,"text":"their passports were confiscated."},{"time":666677,"text":"Some of the men were beaten\nand held at gunpoint."},{"time":669791,"text":"They worked so hard\nthey fainted in the fields."},{"time":674138,"text":"This case hit me so hard."}]},{"cues":[{"time":677572,"text":"After I came back home,"},{"time":679677,"text":"I was wandering through the grocery store,\nand I froze in the produce department."},{"time":684688,"text":"I was remembering the over-the-top meals\nthe Global Horizons survivors"},{"time":688108,"text":"would make for me every time\nI showed up to interview them."},{"time":692521,"text":"They finished one meal with this plate\nof perfect, long-stemmed strawberries,"},{"time":697447,"text":"and as they handed them to me, they said,"},{"time":699984,"text":"\"Aren't these the kind of strawberries\nyou eat with somebody special"},{"time":703240,"text":"in the States?"},{"time":705091,"text":"And don't they taste so much better"},{"time":706925,"text":"when you know the people\nwhose hands picked them for you?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":714016,"text":"As I stood in that grocery store weeks\nlater, I realized I had no idea"},{"time":718271,"text":"of who to thank for this plenty,"},{"time":720471,"text":"and no idea of how\nthey were being treated."},{"time":723569,"text":"So, like the journalist I am, I started\ndigging into the agricultural sector."},{"time":728423,"text":"And I found there are too many fields,\nand too few labor inspectors."},{"time":733119,"text":"I found multiple layers\nof plausible deniability"},{"time":735993,"text":"between grower and distributor\nand processor, and God knows who else."},{"time":740988,"text":"The Global Horizons survivors had been\nbrought to the States"},{"time":743878,"text":"on a temporary guest worker program."},{"time":746979,"text":"That guest worker program\nties a person's legal status"},{"time":750636,"text":"to his or her employer,"},{"time":752302,"text":"and denies that worker\nthe right to organize."},{"time":756717,"text":"Mind you, none of what I am describing\nabout this agricultural sector"},{"time":760993,"text":"or the guest worker program\nis actually human trafficking."},{"time":765234,"text":"It is merely what we find\nlegally tolerable."},{"time":770305,"text":"And I would argue this is\nfertile ground for exploitation."},{"time":774187,"text":"And all of this had been hidden to me,\nbefore I had tried to understand it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779741,"text":"I wasn't the only person\ngrappling with these issues."},{"time":783045,"text":"Pierre Omidyar, founder of eBay,"},{"time":785233,"text":"is one of the biggest anti-trafficking\nphilanthropists in the world."},{"time":789544,"text":"And even he wound up accidentally\ninvesting nearly 10 million dollars"},{"time":794709,"text":"in the pineapple plantation cited\nas having the worst working conditions"},{"time":798393,"text":"in that Global Horizons case."},{"time":802464,"text":"When he found out, he and his wife\nwere shocked and horrified,"},{"time":806458,"text":"and they wound up writing\nan op-ed for a newspaper,"},{"time":809075,"text":"saying that it was up to all of us\nto learn everything we can"},{"time":812998,"text":"about the labor and supply chains\nof the products that we support."},{"time":817909,"text":"I totally agree."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821160,"text":"What would happen\nif each one of us decided"},{"time":823797,"text":"that we are no longer going\nto support companies"},{"time":826378,"text":"if they don't eliminate exploitation\nfrom their labor and supply chains?"},{"time":830326,"text":"If we demanded laws calling for the same?"},{"time":833729,"text":"If all the CEOs out there decided"},{"time":836651,"text":"that they were going to go through\ntheir businesses and say, \"no more\"?"},{"time":841046,"text":"If we ended recruitment fees\nfor migrant workers?"},{"time":844574,"text":"If we decided that guest workers\nshould have the right to organize"},{"time":847709,"text":"without fear of retaliation?"},{"time":849968,"text":"These would be decisions heard\naround the world."},{"time":854729,"text":"This isn't a matter of buying\na fair-trade peach"},{"time":857007,"text":"and calling it a day, buying\na guilt-free zone with your money."},{"time":861188,"text":"That's not how it works."},{"time":863402,"text":"This is the decision to change\na system that is broken,"},{"time":867452,"text":"and that we have unwittingly but willingly"},{"time":870987,"text":"allowed ourselves to profit from\nand benefit from for too long."}]},{"cues":[{"time":877435,"text":"We often dwell on human trafficking\nsurvivors' victimization."},{"time":882303,"text":"But that is not my experience of them."},{"time":885725,"text":"Over all the years that I've\nbeen talking to them,"},{"time":888106,"text":"they have taught me that we are\nmore than our worst days."},{"time":891941,"text":"Each one of us is more\nthan what we have lived through."},{"time":896183,"text":"Especially trafficking survivors."},{"time":898746,"text":"These people were the most resourceful\nand resilient and responsible"},{"time":902393,"text":"in their communities."},{"time":904022,"text":"They were the people that you\nwould take a gamble on."},{"time":907084,"text":"You'd say, I'm gong to sell my rings,\nbecause I have the chance"},{"time":910290,"text":"to send you off to a better future."},{"time":913390,"text":"They were the emissaries of hope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":917371,"text":"These survivors don't need saving."},{"time":920731,"text":"They need solidarity,\nbecause they're behind"},{"time":923799,"text":"some of the most exciting\nsocial justice movements out there today."},{"time":928766,"text":"The nannies and housekeepers\nwho marched with their families"},{"time":931727,"text":"and their employers' families --"},{"time":933651,"text":"their activism got us\nan international treaty"},{"time":936593,"text":"on domestic workers' rights."},{"time":939284,"text":"The Nepali women who were trafficked\ninto the sex trade --"},{"time":943303,"text":"they came together, and they decided"},{"time":945074,"text":"that they were going to make the world's\nfirst anti-trafficking organization"},{"time":948695,"text":"actually headed and run\nby trafficking survivors themselves."},{"time":953681,"text":"These Indian shipyard workers\nwere trafficked"},{"time":956483,"text":"to do post-Hurricane Katrina\nreconstruction."},{"time":959541,"text":"They were threatened with deportation,\nbut they broke out of their work compound"},{"time":963339,"text":"and they marched from New Orleans\nto Washington, D.C.,"},{"time":966742,"text":"to protest labor exploitation."},{"time":969778,"text":"They cofounded an organization called\nthe National Guest Worker Alliance,"},{"time":973317,"text":"and through this organization,\nthey have wound up helping other workers"},{"time":978025,"text":"bring to light exploitation\nand abuses in supply chains"},{"time":982447,"text":"in Walmart and Hershey's factories."},{"time":984139,"text":"And although the Department\nof Justice declined to take their case,"},{"time":988344,"text":"a team of civil rights lawyers won\nthe first of a dozen civil suits"},{"time":992610,"text":"this February, and got\ntheir clients 14 million dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":998260,"text":"These survivors are fighting\nfor people they don't even know yet,"},{"time":1002541,"text":"other workers, and for the possibility\nof a just world for all of us."},{"time":1007626,"text":"This is our chance to do the same."},{"time":1010716,"text":"This is our chance to make the decision"},{"time":1012923,"text":"that tells us who we are,\nas a people and as a society;"},{"time":1016778,"text":"that our prosperity is no\nlonger prosperity,"},{"time":1019649,"text":"as long as it is pinned\nto other people's pain;"},{"time":1023561,"text":"that our lives are\ninextricably woven together;"},{"time":1027193,"text":"and that we have the power\nto make a different choice."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1034217,"text":"I was so reluctant to share\nmy story of my auntie with you."},{"time":1039976,"text":"Before I started this TED process\nand climbed up on this stage,"},{"time":1042977,"text":"I had told literally a handful\nof people about it,"},{"time":1045977,"text":"because, like many a journalist,"},{"time":1047953,"text":"I am far more interested in learning\nabout your stories"},{"time":1050867,"text":"than sharing much,\nif anything, about my own."},{"time":1055273,"text":"I also haven't done my journalistic\ndue diligence on this."},{"time":1058242,"text":"I haven't issued my mountains\nof document requests,"},{"time":1060670,"text":"and interviewed everyone and their mother,"},{"time":1062931,"text":"and I haven't found my auntie yet."},{"time":1065241,"text":"I don't know her story\nof what happened, and of her life now."},{"time":1070781,"text":"The story as I've told it to you\nis messy and unfinished."},{"time":1074914,"text":"But I think it mirrors the messy\nand unfinished situation we're all in,"},{"time":1079790,"text":"when it comes to human trafficking."},{"time":1082523,"text":"We are all implicated in this problem."},{"time":1086291,"text":"But that means we are all\nalso part of its solution."},{"time":1092241,"text":"Figuring out how to build a more\njust world is our work to do,"},{"time":1096379,"text":"and our story to tell."},{"time":1099289,"text":"So let us tell it the way\nwe should have done,"},{"time":1101701,"text":"from the very beginning."},{"time":1103801,"text":"Let us tell this story together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1107518,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1108851,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}